{"entity1": "Controller", "entity2": "Personal Data", "description": "The (Controller, Personal Data) relation defines the responsibilities and obligations of a data controller regarding the management of personal data. The controller is the entity that determines the purposes and duration of processing operations, ensuring that all collection, processing, and storage activities are conducted for specific purposes and based on valid legal bases. They are responsible for ensuring that any further processing remains compatible with the original purposes and must inform the data subject if those purposes change.\n\nIn terms of data governance, the controller is tasked with ensuring the accuracy, security, and lawful processing of personal data, while maintaining overall accountability. This includes managing the storage period and ensuring the timely erasure or rectification of data. Notably, the controller should not retain personal data solely to react to potential requests. Additionally, the controller is responsible for identifying the data subject when necessary and providing copies of their data upon request.\n\nThe controller holds full responsibility and liability for all processing activities carried out by them or on their behalf, ensuring compliance with the Regulation. This oversight extends to the transfer of personal data to third countries or international organizations. Furthermore, when conducting research or archiving, the controller must assess whether the objectives can be achieved using data that does not identify the data subjects. In certain instances, the controller may also be required to transmit personal data to another controller."}
