{"entity": "AI System", "type": "artifact", "description": "An AI System is a machine-based technological entity designed to infer outputs—such as predictions, content, recommendations, or decisions—by deriving models or algorithms from inputs or data. Operating with varying levels of autonomy and adaptiveness, these systems can consist of integrated components, tools, and services, including AI models and user interfaces, to influence their environments. They are utilized across a broad spectrum of domains, including military, civilian, humanitarian, scientific research, and national security, serving purposes that range from improving human activity and detecting decision-making patterns to performing preparatory tasks.

Specific applications of an AI System include remote biometric identification, biometric verification, biometric categorization, and emotion recognition. Because these systems can generate or manipulate content and profile natural persons, they are often subject to regulatory oversight, including transparency obligations and strict guarantees regarding privacy and personal data protection throughout their lifecycle.

A critical distinction is made between AI systems based on their risk level. An AI System may be classified as high-risk if its intended purpose or use case poses a potential threat to health, safety, the environment, or fundamental rights. Such high-risk systems are subject to rigorous regulatory compliance, including conformity assessments, the maintenance of technical documentation, the use of quality training data, and monitoring of performance, capabilities, and limitations.

Depending on their classification and the gravity of any infringements, an AI System may be required to undergo substantial modification, recall, or withdrawal from the market. Whether categorized as general-purpose or high-risk, these systems are characterized by their trade name, intended purpose, and operating logic, and must meet essential requirements to be legally placed on the market or put into service."}
