{"entity": "Data Minimisation", "type": "concept", "description": "A principle of data protection requiring that only necessary personal data be processed.<SEP>A principle under Union data protection law stating that personal data processing should be limited to what is necessary.<SEP>A principle ensuring that personal data processing is limited to what is necessary for the intended purposes.<SEP>A principle requiring that personal data be adequate, relevant, and limited to what is necessary for the purposes for which they are processed.><SEP>Data minimisation is a data-protection principle ensuring that only necessary personal data for a specific purpose are processed.<SEP>Data minimisation is a principle ensuring that personal data processing is limited to what is necessary, especially for archiving, research, or statistical purposes.<SEP>Data minimisation is a principle ensuring that personal data processing is limited to what is necessary for the purposes for which they are processed."}
