Within its jurisdiction, the Union focuses heavily on data governance and the protection of natural persons. It seeks to ensure a coherent data protection framework and the free movement of personal data, providing the legal basis for processing and data transfers. The Union's laws regulate personal data protection, subject rights, and the conditions under which general public, economic, or financial interests may justify restrictions on data processing. Additionally, the Union is the entity within which the Board is established as an independent body and where codes of conduct may hold general validity.

Beyond data protection, the Union promotes the development of trustworthy AI systems and enforces strict obligations for high-risk AI. To achieve this, it mandates the uniform implementation of AI regulatory sandboxes and governs liability laws for AI systems placed on its market. Internationally, the Union acts as a signatory to the United Nations Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities and is the authority responsible for concluding agreements with third countries regarding the recognition and operation of conformity assessment bodies."}
