{"entity1": "Data Subject", "entity2": "Personal Data", "description": "The relation (Data Subject, Personal Data) describes the fundamental connection between an identified or identifiable individual, known as the data subject, and the personal data that relates to them. In this relationship, the data subject is the person whose information is processed, and their vital interests, rights, and freedoms must be safeguarded throughout the processing lifecycle. Because processing personal data can introduce risks to these freedoms, the data subject's consent is generally required for disclosure outside of certain authorized bodies.\n\nThe data subject possesses a comprehensive set of rights to maintain control over their personal data. These include the right to be informed about the purposes of processing and the right to monitor and verify the lawfulness of how their data is handled. Specifically, the data subject has the right to obtain confirmation and communication regarding the personal data being processed, as well as the right of access to that data.\n\nFurthermore, the data subject is entitled to several corrective and restrictive rights, including the rights to rectification (correcting inaccurate data), erasure (the right to be forgotten or delete data), and the restriction of processing. They also possess the right to data portability and the right to object to the processing of their information. Together, these rights ensure that the data subject can request the erasure of their data and maintain overarching authority over its use."}
