- (16) The notion of 'biometric categorisation' referred to in this Regulation should be defined as assigning natural persons to specific categories on the basis of their biometric data. Such specific categories can relate to aspects such as sex, age,  hair  colour,  eye colour, tattoos, behavioural"}
